docs.abstract: The government’s antitrust case against Google borrows heavily from the landmark lawsuit against Microsoft 25 years ago. But it lacks the same cultural impact.
docs.snippet: The government’s antitrust case against Google borrows heavily from the landmark lawsuit against Microsoft 25 years ago. But it lacks the same cultural impact.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Justice Department argues in a federal antitrust suit that Google is a dominant tech company that has abused its market power to bully industry partners, protect its monopoly and thwart competition.

headline.main: Microsoft, Google and Antitrust: Similar Legal Theories in a Different Era
headline.print_headline: Likening Google’s Antitrust Trial to Microsoft’s

docs.abstract: Mortal Kombat, Super Mario Bros. and more are coming this season.
docs.snippet: Mortal Kombat, Super Mario Bros. and more are coming this season.
docs.lead_paragraph: It has been such a fruitful year for video games that you couldn’t blame someone for wanting a light fall lineup to finish titles like Tears of the Kingdom and Baldur’s Gate 3. For better or worse, this season is stacked with AAA releases, long-awaited sequels and promising independent games. (Some games will be available before their official launch dates because of early-access programs.)

docs.abstract: The government states that data is “oxygen for a search engine” and that Google’s anticompetitive behavior has given it a data fortress. Google says innovation explains its success.
docs.snippet: The government states that data is “oxygen for a search engine” and that Google’s anticompetitive behavior has given it a data fortress. Google says innovation explains its success.
docs.lead_paragraph: The federal government’s first monopoly trial of the modern internet era is less than a week old, but already a central character has emerged: data. Its role, its use and its power are key issues in the Justice Department’s case against Google.

headline.main: A Key Question in Google’s Trial: How Formidable Is Its Data Advantage?
headline.print_headline: Data Edge Of Google Is Key Issue

docs.abstract: Britain’s antitrust regulator said the companies had addressed its main concerns about the $69 billion deal, though final approval is yet to come.
docs.snippet: Britain’s antitrust regulator said the companies had addressed its main concerns about the $69 billion deal, though final approval is yet to come.
docs.lead_paragraph: Microsoft came one step closer on Friday to completing its $69 billion purchase of the video game maker Activision Blizzard, in a deal that has become an example of how a company can successfully ride out stricter regulatory scrutiny of the power of tech giants.

headline.main: Microsoft Closes In on Activision Deal After Britain Signals Approval
headline.print_headline: Reversal in Britain Favors Microsoft-Activision Deal

docs.abstract: The suit, filed with the Authors Guild, accuses the A.I. company of infringing on authors’ copyrights, claiming it used their books to train its ChatGPT chatbot.
docs.snippet: The suit, filed with the Authors Guild, accuses the A.I. company of infringing on authors’ copyrights, claiming it used their books to train its ChatGPT chatbot.
docs.lead_paragraph: A group of prominent novelists, including John Grisham, Jonathan Franzen and Elin Hilderbrand, are joining the legal battle against OpenAI over its chatbot technology, as fears about the encroachment of artificial intelligence on creative industries continue to grow.

headline.main: Franzen, Grisham and Other Prominent Authors Sue OpenAI
